suffered from anxiety]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132136590.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A 66-year-old pilot named Liu faced a harrowing battle with anxiety and suicidal thoughts, culminating in a crash into the CITIC Group headquarters, the tallest building in Beijing. The aircraft, which took off after a routine flight, strayed off its intended path, resulting in injuries to 13 individuals. This alarming incident has ignited serious discussions about aviation security in a city known for its stringent controls.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/wrote-about-ending-his-life-pilot-who-hit-beijings-tallest-building-suffered-from-anxiety/articleshow/132136590.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/wrote-about-ending-his-life-pilot-who-hit-beijings-tallest-building-suffered-from-anxiety/articleshow/132136590.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-02T16:12:24+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132136636,imgsize-76136.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iraqi 'Godfather of traffickers' found in UK seeking asylum under changed identity]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132135955.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/iraqi-godfather-of-traffickers-found-in-uk-seeking-asylum-under-changed-identity/articleshow/132135955.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/iraqi-godfather-of-traffickers-found-in-uk-seeking-asylum-under-changed-identity/articleshow/132135955.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-02T15:59:36+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132136230,imgsize-144184.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[From grief support to robot cafes &amp; marriage prospects: How AI is transforming daily life in South Korea]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132133753.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[South Korea is rapidly integrating AI and robotics into daily life, from recreating deceased loved ones to powering unstaffed businesses. This surge is driven by an aging population and a national strategy to become a global AI leader, with massive investments in chips and robotics. The AI boom is also reshaping careers, making semiconductor engineers highly sought-after and influencing educational choices.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/from-grief-support-to-robot-cafes-how-ai-robots-are-transforming-daily-life-in-south-korea/articleshow/132133753.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/from-grief-support-to-robot-cafes-how-ai-robots-are-transforming-daily-life-in-south-korea/articleshow/132133753.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-02T14:51:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132134778,imgsize-210701.cms"/></item></channel></rss>